HEADWORD: Boyne
<hw>Boyne</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a battle in the War of the Grand
Alliance in Ireland in 1690, where William III of England defeated the
deposed James II and so ended Stuart Catholicism in England.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> battle of Boyne, battle of the Boyne.</syn>⟦br⟧
